1
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,918
=Vanished Name=

2
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,894
=Episode 4=
(Everyone Has Secrets)

3
00:01:40,184 --> 00:01:41,865
Three, two, one.

4
00:01:48,184 --> 00:01:49,065
Be careful.

5
00:01:51,785 --> 00:01:54,624
Xiaoyu, do you like it? Xiaoyu?

6
00:01:54,984 --> 00:01:55,705
I do.

7
00:01:55,705 --> 00:01:56,425
Really?

8
00:01:56,945 --> 00:02:01,665
Go ask Mom if she likes
the birthday party I gave you. Go.

9
00:02:07,264 --> 00:02:10,825
Mom, do you like the birthday party
Grandma set up for me?

10
00:02:16,824 --> 00:02:19,704
Mom, look!
It's Princess Xiangsha's dress.

11
00:02:19,704 --> 00:02:21,184
I really like it.

12
00:02:21,985 --> 00:02:27,105
Here we go, our little birthday girl.
Whose birthday girl is this pretty?

13
00:02:36,145 --> 00:02:38,385
Come on! Blow out the candles.

14
00:02:48,888 --> 00:02:52,315
(2004)

15
00:03:13,425 --> 00:03:14,145
Where did you go?

16
00:03:15,504 --> 00:03:17,184
Why are you back so late?

17
00:03:18,545 --> 00:03:20,464
I'm worrying about you.
Don't you know that?

18
00:03:22,825 --> 00:03:24,025
We had an evening self-study.

19
00:03:24,425 --> 00:03:25,385
Evening self-study?

20
00:03:27,305 --> 00:03:29,385
Why didn't you tell me
when you left this morning?

21
00:03:30,224 --> 00:03:31,344
It was added last minute.

22
00:03:31,825 --> 00:03:33,385
Which teacher did it last minute?

23
00:03:34,624 --> 00:03:35,305
Ms. Zhou.

24
00:03:43,985 --> 00:03:44,784
Wash your hands.

25
00:04:16,224 --> 00:04:16,864
Let's eat.

26
00:04:18,505 --> 00:04:20,464
I have a lot of homework.
I have to do it now.

27
00:04:21,664 --> 00:04:23,025
Finish eating first.

28
00:04:24,464 --> 00:04:25,176
I'm not hungry.

29
00:04:27,672 --> 00:04:28,784
You've eaten?

30
00:04:30,265 --> 00:04:32,424
I ate the bread and egg
I brought this morning.

31
00:04:36,385 --> 00:04:37,265
Then don't eat.

32
00:05:21,945 --> 00:05:23,904
Apple I peeled for you
when I was waiting.

33
00:05:25,065 --> 00:05:26,864
Eat it if you want, or throw it away.

34
00:05:29,104 --> 00:05:29,945
Handle it yourself.

35
00:06:01,145 --> 00:06:02,745
Change clothes before doing homework.

36
00:06:20,385 --> 00:06:21,984
You came back late today.

37
00:06:22,385 --> 00:06:24,625
Limit homework time to within one hour.

38
00:06:24,705 --> 00:06:26,825
One hour later,
turn off the lights and go to sleep.

39
00:06:44,065 --> 00:06:45,505
I'll be here with you.

40
00:07:30,008 --> 00:07:32,585
(2023, Qingzhou)

41
00:07:32,585 --> 00:07:33,272
Password correct.

42
00:07:44,025 --> 00:07:45,624
How did you even come up with that?

43
00:07:47,320 --> 00:07:48,945
Hiding a diary in a block of ice?

44
00:08:08,464 --> 00:08:10,264
First, you had to wrap it well,

45
00:08:11,320 --> 00:08:12,625
so it wouldn't leak,

46
00:08:13,505 --> 00:08:15,145
and then freeze it quickly.

47
00:08:16,585 --> 00:08:19,864
Impressive, Mr. Liu. Quite the effort.

48
00:08:27,185 --> 00:08:28,664
Are you mocking me for never cooking?

49
00:08:29,424 --> 00:08:30,544
Let's have a proper talk.

50
00:08:31,265 --> 00:08:33,865
I have the most solid evidence now.
I can surely win if I sue.

51
00:08:35,345 --> 00:08:36,824
What right do you have to talk to me?

52
00:08:37,385 --> 00:08:38,424
We're husband and wife.

53
00:08:40,064 --> 00:08:42,584
Not about rights, just about love.

54
00:08:47,385 --> 00:08:51,105
When I was hospitalized,
I didn't even know if I could survive.

55
00:08:51,865 --> 00:08:54,505
Yet you rummaged through the house
to find my diary,

56
00:08:54,584 --> 00:08:57,625
copied it all, and then hid it away.

57
00:08:58,265 --> 00:09:00,904
I asked you where it was,
and you said you don't know anything.

58
00:09:03,505 --> 00:09:06,865
And this is the love
you talk about? Love?

59
00:09:08,145 --> 00:09:11,184
You hid the diary to cover up
the fact that you plagiarized.

60
00:09:12,385 --> 00:09:14,184
You were afraid I'd use it
to against you.

61
00:09:15,736 --> 00:09:16,824
I'm sorry, Xiaoming.

62
00:09:18,872 --> 00:09:20,105
Think about it.

63
00:09:20,904 --> 00:09:24,385
If I really wanted to destroy it,
to take this to the extreme,

64
00:09:24,465 --> 00:09:27,025
I could have just burned it,
but I didn't.

65
00:09:27,664 --> 00:09:31,544
I knew it was important to you,
so I kept it.

66
00:09:31,584 --> 00:09:34,025
So I should thank you, Mr. Liu?

67
00:09:34,664 --> 00:09:37,145
Thank you for stealing my diary
and not burning it?

68
00:09:37,704 --> 00:09:39,184
Even leaving me a little hope?

69
00:09:42,664 --> 00:09:43,664
You're so shameless.

70
00:09:44,025 --> 00:09:45,064
Don't say that.

71
00:09:45,225 --> 00:09:46,385
Then what should I say?

72
00:09:48,385 --> 00:09:52,745
You're the teacher.
Why don't you teach me how?

73
00:10:37,584 --> 00:10:38,584
I'm doomed.

74
00:10:39,625 --> 00:10:44,465
If you take that diary out, I'm doomed.

75
00:10:47,225 --> 00:10:48,265
So as our family.

76
00:10:49,304 --> 00:10:52,184
All my years of hard work and effort

77
00:10:55,105 --> 00:10:55,985
will also be ruined.

78
00:11:01,464 --> 00:11:03,584
I thought you shouldn't take them,
which were no good.

79
00:11:04,152 --> 00:11:05,432
I can't sleep without the pills.

80
00:11:07,832 --> 00:11:09,385
Others might not know, but don't you?

81
00:11:12,064 --> 00:11:14,304
I've been under so much mental stress
all these years.

82
00:11:15,768 --> 00:11:19,800
Chen Junhang was right.
I'm someone who survives

83
00:11:21,592 --> 00:11:22,584
on my persona.

84
00:11:23,145 --> 00:11:25,745
All the contracts I am carrying
are all for my persona.

85
00:11:26,304 --> 00:11:31,145
If anything goes wrong,
I face huge compensation payments.

86
00:11:33,304 --> 00:11:35,000
It would be a number

87
00:11:37,144 --> 00:11:38,584
I could never afford in my lifetime.

88
00:11:40,145 --> 00:11:41,625
(We've been in the battle of wits,)

89
00:11:42,664 --> 00:11:44,265
(but when I saw him take the pills,)

90
00:11:46,625 --> 00:11:48,385
(I could only give him one last chance.)

91
00:11:49,424 --> 00:11:49,944
Fine.

92
00:11:52,745 --> 00:11:56,385
You go to the publisher yourself
and take the new books off the shelves.

93
00:11:58,584 --> 00:12:00,064
We can settle this privately.

94
00:12:02,544 --> 00:12:03,784
We don't have to go to court.

95
00:12:10,865 --> 00:12:13,025
Xiaoming, can you...

96
00:12:13,025 --> 00:12:13,944
This is my bottom line.

97
00:12:14,544 --> 00:12:19,584
Take one more step forward,
and I'll take back what I just said.

98
00:12:21,584 --> 00:12:22,184
Okay.

99
00:12:25,704 --> 00:12:27,424
Can you give me one day?

100
00:12:28,225 --> 00:12:28,824
Just one day.

101
00:12:42,105 --> 00:12:43,105
There's news on the pen.

102
00:12:49,025 --> 00:12:51,845
This pen is custom-made by a high-end
handmade pen shop in Shanghai.

103
00:12:52,304 --> 00:12:54,385
Each pen has its own
custom serial number.

104
00:12:54,552 --> 00:12:56,376
The one who bought this pen
is named Zhou Yun.

105
00:12:56,745 --> 00:12:59,005
When we checked the staff roster
of Qidian Middle School,

106
00:12:59,005 --> 00:13:00,424
we also found a Zhou Yun.

107
00:13:00,696 --> 00:13:03,192
(Qidian Middle School)
However, she resigned after teaching

108
00:13:03,192 --> 00:13:05,505
the graduating class
of 2004 junior high.

109
00:13:06,064 --> 00:13:07,265
Class of 2004?

110
00:13:07,544 --> 00:13:10,865
- Right.
- Class of 2004? Wasn't that your class?

111
00:13:23,128 --> 00:13:24,056
Meng, what's wrong?

112
00:13:24,184 --> 00:13:27,145
Can I ask you about someone? Zhou Yun.

113
00:13:27,465 --> 00:13:31,576
The teacher who got you and Bai Shu
through junior high graduation.

114
00:13:31,576 --> 00:13:32,704
Any memories?

115
00:13:32,985 --> 00:13:33,985
Ms. Zhou?

116
00:13:34,985 --> 00:13:38,465
I'm Zhou Yun, Chinese and homeroom
teacher for Class 3, Grade 9.

117
00:13:38,625 --> 00:13:39,704
You'll be in my class.

118
00:13:41,304 --> 00:13:42,265
Hello, Ms. Zhou.

119
00:13:44,025 --> 00:13:44,824
Let's shake hands.

120
00:13:46,385 --> 00:13:47,924
Xiaoming?

121
00:13:48,184 --> 00:13:50,385
Why aren't you answering?
Are you still there?

122
00:13:51,105 --> 00:13:52,284
I'm here. I...

123
00:13:52,625 --> 00:13:55,265
Why are you suddenly asking about her?
What's going on?

124
00:13:56,025 --> 00:13:56,865
Asking for someone.

125
00:13:57,625 --> 00:14:01,304
I'll send you some photos.
See if anyone looks familiar.

126
00:14:02,832 --> 00:14:03,832
(Ren Xiaoming)

127
00:14:11,064 --> 00:14:12,125
Did you get the photos?

128
00:14:13,064 --> 00:14:15,184
(Li Meng)
So, any look familiar?

129
00:14:26,944 --> 00:14:28,944
The red pen in the third photo
was Ms. Zhou's.

130
00:14:29,465 --> 00:14:30,225
Are you sure?

131
00:14:30,424 --> 00:14:33,784
I'm sure. That pen was very distinctive.

132
00:14:34,985 --> 00:14:37,345
Okay, got it. Thanks.
I won't bother you anymore.

133
00:14:37,625 --> 00:14:39,865
When I come to Qingzhou,
let's grab a meal together.

134
00:14:42,385 --> 00:14:45,544
(This pen. Ms. Zhou.)

135
00:14:49,784 --> 00:14:51,904
- Follow this lead on Zhou Yun
- Huang Yue.

136
00:14:51,904 --> 00:14:52,865
and find Zhou Yun.

137
00:14:59,765 --> 00:15:02,865
(2004, Qidaohezi Qidian Middle School)

138
00:15:02,865 --> 00:15:03,664
Ren Xiaoming.

139
00:15:06,265 --> 00:15:06,865
Have a seat.

140
00:15:07,304 --> 00:15:12,544
Here. Your essay was quite good.
This is my feedback.

141
00:15:12,784 --> 00:15:15,105
Face yourself. Always be honest.

142
00:15:15,664 --> 00:15:18,664
In writing, you possess
a very valuable quality.

143
00:15:18,824 --> 00:15:19,904
It's honesty.

144
00:15:21,145 --> 00:15:24,345
When someone faces themselves
and can maintain honest,

145
00:15:24,745 --> 00:15:25,865
that is truly remarkable.

146
00:15:27,664 --> 00:15:28,704
A book for you.

147
00:15:30,865 --> 00:15:34,265
A Hundred Years of Different Paths?
I noticed Bai Shu is reading it too.

148
00:15:34,664 --> 00:15:36,904
Yes, she really likes it.

149
00:15:37,424 --> 00:15:39,824
When you finish it,
we can discuss it together.

150
00:15:40,625 --> 00:15:41,704
Thank you, Ms. Zhou.

151
00:15:48,625 --> 00:15:51,424
I've noticed you get nervous easily.

152
00:15:52,865 --> 00:15:55,745
Relax. Don't be afraid
of how others look at you.

153
00:15:56,625 --> 00:15:58,184
Just do what you want to do.

154
00:16:03,304 --> 00:16:04,064
Okay.

155
00:16:14,145 --> 00:16:18,304
(No adult had ever spoken to me
in such an equal tone before.)

156
00:16:27,544 --> 00:16:29,464
(Face yourself. Always be honest)

157
00:16:40,088 --> 00:16:42,345
(Face yourself. Always be honest)

158
00:16:42,345 --> 00:16:43,145
What are you doing?

159
00:16:55,352 --> 00:16:57,032
Two hours until school ends
and trash duty.

160
00:16:57,592 --> 00:16:59,105
Make sure it is properly destroyed.

161
00:17:01,850 --> 00:17:03,610
Wait for me after school.
Let's go somewhere.

162
00:17:08,384 --> 00:17:09,434
The gods deemed

163
00:17:09,434 --> 00:17:12,784
there was no punishment more severe
than performing this hopeless, futile labor

164
00:17:12,985 --> 00:17:14,225
- than this.
- Hurry up.

165
00:17:14,745 --> 00:17:18,505
In Sisyphus,
we see only this one image...

166
00:17:18,844 --> 00:17:19,344
Ms. Zhou.

167
00:17:19,344 --> 00:17:19,844
A...

168
00:17:23,448 --> 00:17:24,216
Come in.

169
00:17:25,624 --> 00:17:26,505
Sit over there.

170
00:17:27,304 --> 00:17:30,905
A tense body, repeating the same motion
a thousand times over.

171
00:17:31,384 --> 00:17:34,185
They are rolling the boulder,
rolling it,

172
00:17:34,384 --> 00:17:36,064
and pushing it
to the top of the mountain.

173
00:17:37,425 --> 00:17:38,985
This book also says,

174
00:17:39,665 --> 00:17:43,144
"We live. Live with the cracks
the world has given us."

175
00:17:43,864 --> 00:17:47,544
"Use our maimed hands
to soothe each other's wounds,

176
00:17:47,905 --> 00:17:49,624
stubbornly striving towards happiness."

177
00:17:51,265 --> 00:17:54,144
"No fate is a punishment for man."

178
00:17:54,665 --> 00:17:57,384
"As long as one gives their all,
they should be happy."

179
00:17:58,304 --> 00:18:03,104
"Embrace the light of the present,
don't pin hopes on a distant utopia."

180
00:18:03,745 --> 00:18:04,905
"Be energetic and uplifted,

181
00:18:05,265 --> 00:18:07,736
because existence itself
is the most powerful rebellion

182
00:18:08,085 --> 00:18:09,624
against the absurd."

183
00:18:11,864 --> 00:18:14,784
Facing the boulder,
Sisyphus chose to do so.

184
00:18:17,144 --> 00:18:19,104
What is the boulder? Who is Sisyphus?

185
00:18:19,104 --> 00:18:22,985
In a moment, you can all close your eyes
and think about it.

186
00:18:23,505 --> 00:18:28,465
Before the countdown ends,
each of us must make a choice.

187
00:18:31,104 --> 00:18:33,104
Alright, the countdown begins.

188
00:18:58,424 --> 00:19:00,728
At first, someone noticed
Ms. Zhou stayed late after work,

189
00:19:00,728 --> 00:19:02,040
grading papers alone.

190
00:19:03,025 --> 00:19:04,705
Then someone went to ask her questions.

191
00:19:05,344 --> 00:19:08,505
More and more people started going,
and it turned into a secret book club.

192
00:19:10,425 --> 00:19:11,544
Thanks for taking me there.

193
00:19:12,144 --> 00:19:13,624
Ms. Zhou told me to bring you.

194
00:19:14,465 --> 00:19:16,225
Ms. Zhou?

195
00:19:18,465 --> 00:19:20,505
But now, I'm taking you somewhere else.

196
00:19:21,025 --> 00:19:21,864
Where are we going?

197
00:19:23,025 --> 00:19:24,064
You'll find out later.

198
00:19:26,064 --> 00:19:28,745
I can't go. I need to buy groceries.

199
00:19:29,064 --> 00:19:30,225
The market is about to close.

200
00:19:32,025 --> 00:19:33,705
Then we'll go another day.

201
00:19:36,144 --> 00:19:36,824
See you tomorrow.

202
00:19:37,624 --> 00:19:38,384
See you tomorrow.

203
00:19:46,584 --> 00:19:47,304
Bai Shu.

204
00:19:49,745 --> 00:19:53,864
I want to go with you.
Let's make it quick.

205
00:20:14,705 --> 00:20:16,025
Why did you bring me here?

206
00:20:22,040 --> 00:20:23,512
(Bai Shu's Tomb)

207
00:20:32,384 --> 00:20:36,864
June 1st, 1989, is my birthday.

208
00:20:39,640 --> 00:20:41,208
(Born June 1, 1977, Died June 1, 1989)

209
00:20:42,064 --> 00:20:43,505
This Bai Shu is the me who died.

210
00:20:46,624 --> 00:20:50,265
I was dead before I was born.

211
00:21:02,705 --> 00:21:03,905
This isn't real.

212
00:21:04,905 --> 00:21:06,265
Inside is another girl.

213
00:21:12,905 --> 00:21:13,905
I'm so strange.

214
00:21:16,584 --> 00:21:18,344
Do you still want to be friends with me?

215
00:21:26,705 --> 00:21:28,505
You told me such a big secret.

216
00:21:29,656 --> 00:21:30,745
I'll always be your friend.

217
00:21:35,064 --> 00:21:36,505
I'll always be your friend too.

218
00:21:42,344 --> 00:21:45,624
(Bai Shu's Tomb)
Is this really your birthday?

219
00:21:48,144 --> 00:21:48,985
Maybe.

220
00:21:53,104 --> 00:21:54,344
Was she really named Bai Shu?

221
00:22:02,064 --> 00:22:03,064
That's so coincidental.

222
00:22:04,304 --> 00:22:05,665
1977...

223
00:22:07,705 --> 00:22:09,505
She was only twelve when she died.

224
00:22:10,624 --> 00:22:12,465
Death has stopped her time.

225
00:22:14,064 --> 00:22:18,824
She's trapped here, rotting,
eventually becoming one with the dirt.

226
00:22:21,304 --> 00:22:24,824
But I'm alive.
I have to get out of here.

227
00:22:28,824 --> 00:22:31,064
I want to travel to every corner
of this world someday

228
00:22:32,144 --> 00:22:35,025
to see different people
and observe how they live.

229
00:22:38,505 --> 00:22:39,672
Do you know Sulawesi?

230
00:22:42,072 --> 00:22:44,265
It's an island in central Indonesia.

231
00:22:45,344 --> 00:22:48,544
The Toraja people on Sulawesi
have a unique custom.

232
00:22:49,064 --> 00:22:53,864
Every few years, they dig up
their loved ones' bodies from the graves.

233
00:22:54,360 --> 00:22:56,505
They air the bodies out
and dress them in new clothes.

234
00:22:57,064 --> 00:22:58,824
Then they parade with the bodies.

235
00:22:59,505 --> 00:23:01,705
After the ceremony,
they rebury the bodies.

236
00:23:14,905 --> 00:23:19,265
(She has a tomb bearing her exact name,
and a dream to travel the world.)

237
00:23:19,985 --> 00:23:22,465
(But me? I have nothing.)

238
00:23:25,505 --> 00:23:29,064
Let's go. I have to go home
and cook for my brother.

239
00:23:38,665 --> 00:23:39,705
I am mad.

240
00:23:44,304 --> 00:23:45,505
But I'm not mad at you.

241
00:23:47,896 --> 00:23:49,784
I'm mad that I have to go cook
for my brother.

242
00:23:56,104 --> 00:23:57,064
Let's go.

243
00:24:19,624 --> 00:24:20,745
The curtains.

244
00:24:30,624 --> 00:24:31,624
Where have you been?

245
00:24:31,624 --> 00:24:32,124
Mom.

246
00:24:33,240 --> 00:24:34,104
My classmate and I...

247
00:24:34,104 --> 00:24:35,025
Boy or girl?

248
00:24:36,505 --> 00:24:37,384
Girl.

249
00:24:37,425 --> 00:24:38,185
Tell me the truth.

250
00:24:38,344 --> 00:24:39,784
I swear.

251
00:24:51,705 --> 00:24:52,784
What are you doing?

252
00:24:54,544 --> 00:24:56,945
Wait, what are you doing?

253
00:24:57,624 --> 00:25:00,864
Why are you grabbing my clothes?
What are you doing?

254
00:25:01,665 --> 00:25:04,425
Are you crazy?
Why are you smelling my clothes?

255
00:25:04,425 --> 00:25:05,745
Mom! Mom, what are you doing?

256
00:25:05,745 --> 00:25:06,584
What are you doing?

257
00:25:06,584 --> 00:25:07,584
Why are you so late?

258
00:25:07,985 --> 00:25:09,544
We couldn't get a ride.

259
00:25:09,544 --> 00:25:11,905
So we had to walk back.
It took over two hours.

260
00:25:12,064 --> 00:25:15,304
Mom, look, her shoes are covered in mud.
She must have walked really far.

261
00:25:20,384 --> 00:25:20,884
I saw it.

262
00:25:23,665 --> 00:25:24,544
Have you eaten?

263
00:25:25,425 --> 00:25:25,985
No.

264
00:25:30,064 --> 00:25:31,985
Mom set up the curtains for you.

265
00:25:43,352 --> 00:25:46,040
Noodles are clumping. Add water.
Late again? I'll break your legs.

266
00:25:46,040 --> 00:25:48,104
Eat it and then explain yourself.
Heard me?

267
00:25:49,344 --> 00:25:50,344
She heard you.

268
00:25:53,905 --> 00:25:57,104
The noodles Mom made today were good.
She saved them just for you.

269
00:26:39,144 --> 00:26:43,025
(After coming back from the cemetery,
Bai Shu's mom picked her up every day,)

270
00:26:44,088 --> 00:26:45,705
(and we never went home together again.)

271
00:26:48,144 --> 00:26:51,144
Why don't you walk home with Zhang Fang
and me after school lately?

272
00:26:52,064 --> 00:26:53,304
You can just go.

273
00:26:54,064 --> 00:26:56,185
What? Can't you walk without me?

274
00:26:56,584 --> 00:26:57,384
Take this.

275
00:27:38,665 --> 00:27:40,064
Where did you get this blouse?

276
00:27:41,265 --> 00:27:42,025
My friend gave me.

277
00:27:42,864 --> 00:27:43,864
Boy or girl?

278
00:27:43,985 --> 00:27:45,064
Not your business.

279
00:27:45,185 --> 00:27:46,425
It must be from a boy.

280
00:27:46,425 --> 00:27:47,544
What are you doing?

281
00:27:47,584 --> 00:27:49,425
Take it off, or don't go to school.

282
00:27:49,705 --> 00:27:50,985
You brat! Take it off!

283
00:27:50,985 --> 00:27:51,945
What?

284
00:27:52,384 --> 00:27:54,265
Accepting gifts at such a young age?

285
00:27:55,304 --> 00:27:56,745
- What?
- Why did he give you a gift?

286
00:27:57,225 --> 00:28:00,344
That year, I had no spine
and accepted a pink shirt.

287
00:28:00,985 --> 00:28:02,185
It ruined my whole life.

288
00:28:07,144 --> 00:28:08,584
Don't point at me!

289
00:28:08,584 --> 00:28:09,745
Give it to me.

290
00:28:11,104 --> 00:28:11,624
Xiaoming.

291
00:28:11,945 --> 00:28:12,824
Give it to me.

292
00:28:13,584 --> 00:28:14,384
Hurry!

293
00:28:14,384 --> 00:28:15,784
Why are you so annoying?

294
00:28:17,384 --> 00:28:19,544
It's all dirty now.
How am I supposed to eat it?

295
00:28:22,624 --> 00:28:24,465
How's the fit on that blouse I gave you?

296
00:28:33,505 --> 00:28:34,505
Did you eat breakfast?

297
00:28:39,304 --> 00:28:39,905
He Yuqiong.

298
00:28:40,465 --> 00:28:42,425
Why are your mom's tea eggs
so delicious?

299
00:28:42,544 --> 00:28:43,044
Right?

300
00:28:43,745 --> 00:28:45,384
Teacher's coming!

301
00:28:45,624 --> 00:28:46,425
Class begins.

302
00:28:47,144 --> 00:28:48,304
All rise.

303
00:28:49,544 --> 00:28:50,425
Good morning, class.

304
00:28:50,584 --> 00:28:53,185
- Good morning, Teacher.
- Good morning, Teacher.

305
00:28:53,185 --> 00:28:54,104
Please sit down.

306
00:28:54,665 --> 00:28:55,985
I've reviewed your homework.

307
00:28:55,985 --> 00:28:56,985
- Good job.
- Who gave me eggs?

308
00:28:56,985 --> 00:28:58,225
We move on to the next chapter.

309
00:28:58,225 --> 00:29:00,504
Open your books.
Let's review the Pythagorean theorem.

310
00:29:22,665 --> 00:29:23,185
Ren Xiaoming.

311
00:29:28,344 --> 00:29:30,624
What's wrong? Why did you
ask Ms. Zhou to change seats?

312
00:29:33,104 --> 00:29:34,985
Are you mute now? What did I do wrong?

313
00:29:34,985 --> 00:29:36,144
Just tell me what's going on.

314
00:29:36,705 --> 00:29:39,384
I can't see clearly.
I need to move up front.

315
00:29:41,745 --> 00:29:45,304
Well, sorry. I didn't know
you're nearsighted.

316
00:29:45,945 --> 00:29:48,104
In that case, go get yourself glasses.

317
00:29:49,784 --> 00:29:51,985
I'm not nearsighted.
My eyes are perfectly fine.

318
00:29:52,144 --> 00:29:53,584
I just don't want to see you.

319
00:29:55,505 --> 00:29:56,265
What did I do?

320
00:29:56,665 --> 00:29:58,784
I just don't want to talk to you.
You're so annoying.

321
00:30:01,185 --> 00:30:02,185
Annoying!

322
00:30:03,985 --> 00:30:05,705
What exactly did I do wrong?

323
00:30:23,544 --> 00:30:26,584
What are you looking at?
Are you some kind of crab?

324
00:30:26,985 --> 00:30:27,905
Why haven't you left?

325
00:30:28,104 --> 00:30:29,185
Didn't your mom come?

326
00:30:30,745 --> 00:30:33,304
Don't wait for me here, idiot.

327
00:30:34,144 --> 00:30:34,905
What did you say?

328
00:30:35,144 --> 00:30:35,784
Nothing.

329
00:30:36,185 --> 00:30:37,344
Let's walk home together.

330
00:30:37,705 --> 00:30:39,104
No. I have to buy groceries.

331
00:30:39,705 --> 00:30:41,584
It's rare for us to walk home once.

332
00:30:51,505 --> 00:30:52,304
Is it your mom?

333
00:30:53,544 --> 00:30:55,985
She's so beautiful and elegant.

334
00:30:56,265 --> 00:30:58,584
I wonder why you got
all these great genes.

335
00:30:59,784 --> 00:31:00,905
What's wrong?

336
00:31:06,824 --> 00:31:07,465
Hello, Madam.

337
00:31:08,104 --> 00:31:09,864
Hello. You're such a good girl.

338
00:31:10,745 --> 00:31:11,985
What's your name?

339
00:31:12,304 --> 00:31:13,384
My name is Ren Xiaoming.

340
00:31:17,665 --> 00:31:18,745
Are you classmates?

341
00:31:19,044 --> 00:31:21,544
Yes, we're in the same class.
We are best friends...

342
00:31:28,945 --> 00:31:30,644
The weather changed today. Here.

343
00:31:31,544 --> 00:31:32,864
Put it on, or you'd catch a cold.

344
00:31:34,265 --> 00:31:35,985
You bought new clothes again?

345
00:31:37,824 --> 00:31:39,604
- Put it on. Let me see.
- Come on.

346
00:31:40,784 --> 00:31:44,104
Looks great. You have such good taste.

347
00:31:44,584 --> 00:31:45,985
You're such a sweet talker.

348
00:31:47,425 --> 00:31:50,745
Xiaoming, come visit my home sometime.

349
00:31:51,225 --> 00:31:52,344
Okay. Goodbye.

350
00:31:53,104 --> 00:31:53,604
Goodbye.

351
00:31:53,665 --> 00:31:54,165
Bye-bye.

352
00:31:54,304 --> 00:31:54,804
Go home.

353
00:31:59,584 --> 00:32:02,505
What's wrong with you?
Why be so grumpy with such a gentle mom?

354
00:32:03,025 --> 00:32:04,584
What are you nudging me for?

355
00:32:09,752 --> 00:32:13,047
(2023, Qingzhou)

356
00:32:13,745 --> 00:32:15,824
Xiaoming, get up and eat your noodles.

357
00:32:23,224 --> 00:32:24,152
How did you get in?

358
00:32:25,240 --> 00:32:26,304
Who let you in?

359
00:32:26,705 --> 00:32:28,505
My son-in-law let me in.

360
00:32:30,185 --> 00:32:31,665
What did your son-in-law say to you?

361
00:32:32,425 --> 00:32:35,665
My son-in-law said he knows he was wrong.
The book was written by you.

362
00:32:37,304 --> 00:32:39,304
Sell the book,
and all the money is yours.

363
00:32:42,064 --> 00:32:44,745
Why do you want to abandon
such a good life? What do you want?

364
00:32:46,304 --> 00:32:47,465
It's just a book.

365
00:32:47,745 --> 00:32:51,265
You wrote me to look like such a mess,
and I didn't even get mad.

366
00:32:52,265 --> 00:32:55,624
I haven't even said I'd sue you
for violating personal privacy.

367
00:32:58,784 --> 00:33:01,945
You don't fight for property ownership,
yet you fight over a lousy book.

368
00:33:02,584 --> 00:33:07,144
Even if you win, you'll have to pay
a lot of money to those publishers.

369
00:33:07,304 --> 00:33:10,465
Isn't that money coming out
of both your pockets? How foolish.

370
00:33:10,505 --> 00:33:11,505
You idiot!

371
00:33:14,905 --> 00:33:18,465
If you ruin Xiaoran, you'll know
just how hard life will be later.

372
00:33:19,225 --> 00:33:20,465
Why?

373
00:33:21,144 --> 00:33:23,225
I'm not like you,
finding one man after another.

374
00:33:23,784 --> 00:33:24,864
I can live without a man.

375
00:33:25,496 --> 00:33:28,152
You have to be divorced to know this.
The yin-yang balance is off.

376
00:33:32,505 --> 00:33:33,025
Hello.

377
00:33:33,265 --> 00:33:34,025
Where are you?

378
00:33:34,505 --> 00:33:35,505
Jogging in the complex.

379
00:33:36,225 --> 00:33:38,304
Come back
and take your reinforcement away.

380
00:33:38,584 --> 00:33:39,425
Send her back home.

381
00:33:41,824 --> 00:33:42,665
What happened?

382
00:33:42,985 --> 00:33:45,505
We had an argument.
She went downstairs out of anger.

383
00:33:50,905 --> 00:33:52,824
Mom.

384
00:33:56,265 --> 00:33:57,584
Xiaoming called me.

385
00:33:58,505 --> 00:33:59,905
The sticky rice buns are smashed.

386
00:34:03,344 --> 00:34:05,344
It's okay. I'll handle it.

387
00:34:06,265 --> 00:34:09,664
Mom, that book I recently published

388
00:34:11,385 --> 00:34:12,425
was written by Xiaoming.

389
00:34:13,825 --> 00:34:14,664
It's all my fault.

390
00:34:16,264 --> 00:34:17,584
I gave him a whole day.

391
00:34:17,584 --> 00:34:21,184
Yet he wasted a whole day,
and even brought my mother here.

392
00:34:22,104 --> 00:34:22,744
That's good.

393
00:34:23,184 --> 00:34:26,224
If it weren't for this call,
I wouldn't even have this evidence.

394
00:34:26,785 --> 00:34:29,345
This evidence is enough to sue,
but it won't win the case.

395
00:34:29,584 --> 00:34:33,144
Without other evidence to back it up,
this alone isn't convincing enough.

396
00:34:35,264 --> 00:34:38,385
Don't you have any other evidence?
Have you found that diary?

397
00:34:38,985 --> 00:34:42,144
Who knows where he hid it?
I really can't find it.

398
00:34:44,505 --> 00:34:45,785
Forget about that one.

399
00:34:48,744 --> 00:34:51,624
Advice for you. Use the threat
of going to court to scare him.

400
00:34:51,825 --> 00:34:55,385
If he doesn't want to make a big deal,
he'll have to settle out of court.

401
00:34:55,385 --> 00:34:56,224
I don't want it.

402
00:34:59,104 --> 00:35:01,224
I want to go to court. It has to happen.

403
00:35:02,465 --> 00:35:03,985
Wait, what do you mean?

404
00:35:04,425 --> 00:35:07,264
Last night, you called me saying
you softened and weren't going to sue.

405
00:35:08,025 --> 00:35:12,345
In just less than a day,
you've changed your mind.

406
00:35:13,584 --> 00:35:15,664
Now it's not just
about copyright anymore.

407
00:35:16,425 --> 00:35:18,865
Now it's the darkest moment of my life.

408
00:35:19,624 --> 00:35:24,624
Since it's a do-or-die battle,
we must go to court.

409
00:35:28,584 --> 00:35:30,425
Mom, what do you think of this place?

410
00:35:32,224 --> 00:35:36,064
Actually, it's just average.
But the value of this place lies here.

411
00:35:37,664 --> 00:35:38,232
Look!

412
00:35:39,736 --> 00:35:40,664
How is it?

413
00:35:41,584 --> 00:35:44,224
With super awesome river view. And here.

414
00:35:44,224 --> 00:35:45,945
Oh, my!

415
00:35:48,505 --> 00:35:50,345
Look. A ferris wheel.

416
00:35:53,945 --> 00:35:54,785
Ferris wheel.

417
00:35:55,505 --> 00:35:56,544
I saw it!

418
00:36:03,785 --> 00:36:06,905
Thank you. You spent so much.

419
00:36:08,945 --> 00:36:09,785
It's only right, Mom.

420
00:36:10,264 --> 00:36:12,920
You rarely visit, so I haven't had
the chance to treat you right.

421
00:36:13,544 --> 00:36:15,224
Just make yourself at home here.

422
00:36:17,985 --> 00:36:20,064
- Ms. Ren, your luggage...
- Bring them in.

423
00:36:20,584 --> 00:36:23,144
Wait, let my son-in-law handle it.

424
00:36:24,825 --> 00:36:25,825
I only trust you.

425
00:36:26,345 --> 00:36:27,025
Alright.

426
00:36:30,905 --> 00:36:32,345
It's so beautiful.

427
00:36:34,785 --> 00:36:37,465
Feels like standing in the sky.

428
00:36:42,865 --> 00:36:43,905
Where should I put this?

429
00:36:49,624 --> 00:36:50,945
You can go now.

430
00:36:52,465 --> 00:36:57,785
Okay, rest early.
Call me if you need anything.

431
00:36:58,385 --> 00:36:59,064
Wait.

432
00:37:01,064 --> 00:37:04,704
Tell Xiaoming to call me.
Let her know I'm here.

433
00:37:05,785 --> 00:37:10,184
If she wants,
have her join me for dinner.

434
00:37:12,905 --> 00:37:15,264
Alright, I'll tell her.

435
00:37:16,345 --> 00:37:19,104
Join you for dinner
to eat sticky rice buns.

436
00:37:19,505 --> 00:37:20,264
Bye, Mom.

437
00:37:20,825 --> 00:37:21,785
Get the door.

438
00:37:21,865 --> 00:37:22,465
Sure.

439
00:37:23,416 --> 00:37:25,048
(Mom: What a presidential suite.
My son-in-law treats me so well!)

440
00:37:44,905 --> 00:37:46,664
How did you know I'd be back right now?

441
00:37:50,945 --> 00:37:52,224
Installed a camera in my car?

442
00:37:53,905 --> 00:37:55,184
I've been waiting here for you.

443
00:37:56,465 --> 00:37:59,264
By blocking my car door?
That's one way to show sincerity?

444
00:38:02,385 --> 00:38:05,664
After I settled Mom in, I drove back.

445
00:38:05,905 --> 00:38:10,144
The whole way here, my heart was heavy,
and I couldn't go upstairs.

446
00:38:11,025 --> 00:38:16,224
You've got it backwards. You called
my mom here to stress me out.

447
00:38:17,224 --> 00:38:20,184
You've really mastered the skill
of playing the victim.

448
00:38:24,104 --> 00:38:26,345
Can we have a proper talk?

449
00:38:30,584 --> 00:38:31,184
Okay.

450
00:38:39,345 --> 00:38:40,345
Let's talk at home.

451
00:38:49,905 --> 00:38:54,025
I forgot we can't talk at home.
There are no cameras here, right?

452
00:38:55,144 --> 00:38:56,825
Fine, let's talk here.

453
00:38:57,184 --> 00:39:02,825
Xiaoming, I sincerely
apologize to you. I was wrong.

454
00:39:03,704 --> 00:39:04,465
About what?

455
00:39:13,905 --> 00:39:15,224
I should take the blame.

456
00:39:16,825 --> 00:39:20,544
During the pandemic,
you were stuck abroad,

457
00:39:20,865 --> 00:39:22,825
and I was cooped up at home
with nowhere to go.

458
00:39:23,224 --> 00:39:26,104
The publisher kept pushing me
to submit the manuscript.

459
00:39:26,264 --> 00:39:29,064
It drove me crazy.
I felt completely drained of ideas.

460
00:39:30,025 --> 00:39:32,440
One day, when I was tidying up

461
00:39:34,584 --> 00:39:36,184
and found your diary.

462
00:39:36,664 --> 00:39:38,104
I just flipped through it casually.

463
00:39:39,224 --> 00:39:42,385
But the more I read,
the more engrossed I became.

464
00:39:42,985 --> 00:39:47,825
It sparked my imagination.
The stories gave me inspiration.

465
00:39:48,264 --> 00:39:51,425
So I wrote day and night,
finishing it in just a month.

466
00:39:52,945 --> 00:39:56,624
The day I finished it was the first time
I had a proper, peaceful meal.

467
00:39:58,664 --> 00:40:00,544
Go on. I'm listening.

468
00:40:03,025 --> 00:40:05,704
I haven't turned on the recorder.
I'm not that fast.

469
00:40:06,584 --> 00:40:08,704
Can we stop this?

470
00:40:08,825 --> 00:40:11,664
Should I turn it on
so you can repeat that?

471
00:40:12,104 --> 00:40:14,305
What's the point
of my saying anything now?

472
00:40:14,744 --> 00:40:16,584
The diary is in your hands.

473
00:40:16,584 --> 00:40:19,425
You're apologizing
only because I have the diary.

474
00:40:20,425 --> 00:40:23,865
How is this apology any different
from bringing my mom here to pressure me?

475
00:40:25,064 --> 00:40:28,744
It's just to make me give in.
I won't accept an apology like that.

476
00:40:29,464 --> 00:40:31,505
I've contacted Liang Yi
and given her the evidence.

477
00:40:31,744 --> 00:40:33,064
I am taking this to court.

478
00:40:33,624 --> 00:40:35,744
Spend your time finding a good lawyer.

479
00:40:36,064 --> 00:40:37,704
D-Do you really have to do this?

480
00:40:37,704 --> 00:40:39,584
Do you really have
to push me over the edge?

481
00:40:39,825 --> 00:40:41,144
I didn't tell you to plagiarize.

482
00:40:41,825 --> 00:40:43,305
Isn't it just about the credit?

483
00:40:43,624 --> 00:40:46,704
You never told me
you cared about the credit before.

484
00:40:47,544 --> 00:40:51,584
It's not about the credit. I care about
every single word in the book.

485
00:40:52,064 --> 00:40:53,345
You crossed my line.

486
00:40:54,144 --> 00:40:57,825
T-That's just a cliché
coming-of-age story, dime a dozen.

487
00:40:58,144 --> 00:40:59,704
T-There's nothing special about it.

488
00:41:08,744 --> 00:41:13,224
Maybe there are five thousand
identical flowers in the world,

489
00:41:14,505 --> 00:41:18,425
but only one is my unique rose.

490
00:41:21,945 --> 00:41:25,104
Can we be mature
and realistic about this?

491
00:41:26,305 --> 00:41:28,064
If the book sells well and makes money,

492
00:41:28,305 --> 00:41:29,305
we'll all benefit.

493
00:41:29,624 --> 00:41:32,905
To me, being mature is to have
the courage to defend what's mine.

494
00:41:33,184 --> 00:41:36,104
Reality is, not everyone
has to listen to you.

495
00:41:36,104 --> 00:41:38,865
Liu Xiaoran, you need to face reality.

496
00:41:40,465 --> 00:41:42,104
I don't have to give you what you want.

497
00:41:42,744 --> 00:41:45,704
If you do this,
you'll leave us both with nothing.

498
00:41:45,704 --> 00:41:46,744
Then so be it.

499
00:41:51,825 --> 00:41:52,865
Can't believe it.

500
00:42:02,224 --> 00:42:02,905
Go.

501
00:42:04,704 --> 00:42:05,704
Why isn't it leashed?

502
00:42:05,985 --> 00:42:08,345
(Under Repair, Out of Service)
Don't you know to leash your dog?

503
00:42:08,792 --> 00:42:10,296
It's so late. I thought no one's out.

504
00:42:10,296 --> 00:42:11,345
Am I not one?

505
00:42:11,505 --> 00:42:12,184
Going or not?

506
00:42:12,264 --> 00:42:13,144
Yes.

507
00:42:14,865 --> 00:42:16,184
What's the rush? Why the hurry?

508
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:12,808
=Vanished Name=
